    caption: [Visualization of DNA replication. Stages in the replication of circular DNA molecules have been visualized by electron microscopy. Replication of a circular chromosome produces a structure resembling the Greek letter theta, (cid:3) , as both strands are replicated simultaneously (new strands shown in light red). The electron micrographs show images of plasmid DNA being replicated from a single replication origin.],
